docs.abstract: When companies funnel money into their own shares, earnings per share look better, but the buybacks can siphon money away from investments in innovation.

docs.lead_paragraph: IPhone sales are down and Apple has run into obstacles in China, its second-most-important market. Investors have beaten down Apple’s once highflying shares this year, and the company’s troubles have been a drag on the entire stock market.

headline.main: Buybacks by Companies Like Apple May Signal Danger, Not Growth
